%2F2024%2F04%2F14%2Fus%2Felections%2Ftimes-siena-poll-registered-voter-crosstabs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiden%20had%20a%20one-point%20lead%20over%20Trump%20among%20voters%20aged%2018%20to%2029%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there's%20no%20guarantee%20these%20voters%20will%20remain%20in%20Trump's%20corner%20in%20November%2C%20the%20Times%20wrote.%20With%20many%20irregular%20voters%20splitting%20their%20tickets%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20already%20being%20seen%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-reelection-swing-state-democrats-baldwin-casey-coattails-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDemocratic%20Senate%20candidates%20in%20swing%20states%20including%20Pennsylvania%20and%20Wisconsin%20are%20running%20ahead%20of%20Biden%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Trump's%20support%20among%20these%20disengaged%20voters%20could%20falter%20as%20partisan%20leanings%20sharpen%20closer%20to%20the%20election.%20Many%20of%20these%20less%20engaged%20voters%20could%20eventually%20support%20Biden%20or%20stay%20at%20home%2C%20said%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20issue%20for%20irregular%20voters%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20economy%2C%20the%20poll%20showed.%20Democratic-leaning%20irregular%20voters%20said%20they%20view%20the%20economy%20as%20either%20%26quot%3Bpoor%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfair%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20Democratic%20voters%20who%20vote%20more%20regularly%2C%20described%20the%20economy%20as%20%26quot%3Bgood%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bexcellent%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20presents%20a%20challenge%20for%20Biden%20as%20he%20aims%20to%20bolster%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-us-economy-would-look-like-with-trump-biden-presidency-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20economic%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20among%20young%20voters%20and%20minorities%20who%20would%20generally%20be%20inclined%20to%20back%20him%20based