urity%20benefits%20was%203.2%25%20in%202024.%20According%20to%20an%20ongoing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fseniorsleague.org%2Fpress-brief-4-10-24-march-cpi-w-comes-in-at-3-5%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CThe%25202024%2520Senior%2520Survey%2520conducted%2Cmore%2520per%2520month%2520in%25202023.%2522%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20by%20The%20Senior%20Citizens%20League%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2071%25%20of%20older%20Americans%20did%20not%20think%20this%20year's%20increase%20was%20enough%20to%20cover%20their%20rising%20bills%20at%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20forecast%20of%20a%202.66%25%20COLA%20for%202025%2C%20it%20appears%20seniors%20will%20continue%20to%20suffer%20financial%20insecurity%20as%20much%20next%20year%20as%20they%20have%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fseniorsleague.org%2Fpress-brief-5-15-24-march-cpi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20Shannon%20Benton%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20The%20Senior%20Citizens%20League.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffaq.ssa.gov%2Fen-us%2FTopic%2Farticle%2FKA-01903%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20average%20monthly%20benefit%20in%202024%20is%20%241%2C907%2C%20up%20about%20%2450%20from%202023.%20According%20to%20Benton%2C%20the%20net%20benefit%20increase%20was%20just%20%2440.20%20after%20the%20cost%20of%20Medicare%20rose%20by%20%249.80%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Senior%20Citizen%20League's%20survey%2C%2043%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20their%20monthly%20expenses%20had%20increased%20by%20at%20least%20%24185%20a%20month%20in%202023%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22older%20man%20in%20orange%20shirt%20and%20glasses%20balances%20his%20head%20on%20his%20hands%20while%20staring%20into%20the%20distance%20with%20palm%20trees%20behind%20him%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6644fed39fc063e829b161f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOver%2067%20million%20Americans%20receive%20Social%20Security.%3Cp%3EIppei%20Naoi%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20Security%20recipients%20typically%20receive%20an%20increase%20in%20their%20benefits%20in%20January%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living.%20The%20exact%20amount%20is%20based%20on%20the%20level%20of%20inflation%20observed%20in%20The%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics'%20consumer%20price%20index%20(CPI)%20from%20July%20through%20September%20of%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost-of-living%20increase%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Foact%2Fcola%2Fcolaseries.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evary%20wildly%20each%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20final%20adjustment%20based%20on%20pre-pandemic%20inflation%2C%20the%20COLA%20was%201.3%25.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20increase%20was%208.7%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%2067%20million%20Americans%20receive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-will-happen-to-social-security-in-default-debt-ceiling-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20an%20increase%20is%20not%20guaranteed.%20Since%20the%20COLA%20was%20added%20to%20Social%20Security%20benefits%20in%201975%2C%20there%20have%20been%20three%20years%20without%20a%20bump%20in%20the%20monthly%20checks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20Americans%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-deals-bulk-items-costco-food-price-comparison-inflation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20appears%20to%20be%20one%20area%20of%20inflation%20that%20is%20hitting%20older%20adults%20the%20hardest.%20In%20The%20Senior%20Citizen%20League's%20sur