ers-with-lithuania-and-finland-vilnius-calls-it-escalation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20was%20a%20calculated%20provocation%20designed%20to%20intimidate%20neighboring%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20further%20proof%20that%20Russia's%20aggressive%20and%20revisionist%20policy%20is%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20security%20of%20neighbouring%20countries%20and%20Europe%20as%20a%20whole%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20department's%20statement%20said%2C%20per%20Lithuanian%20National%20Radio%20and%20Television.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20border%20guards%20last%20week%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Festonia-russia-buoys-border-10b99970ed538ce1684bf88c6384a1ec%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremoved%20around%2024%20of%2050%20buoys%20that%20mark%20shipping%20routes%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Narva%20River%20%E2%80%94%20which%20marks%20the%20border%20with%20Russia%20%E2%80%94%20in%20an%20incident%20that%20EU%20High%20Representative%20Josep%20Borrell%20labeled%20%26quot%3Bunacceptable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20think%20tank%20said%20the%20move%20%26quot%3Bset%20conditions%20to%20further%20question%20maritime%20borders%20and%20test%20NATO%20resolve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20officials%20have%20warned%20that%20Russia%20may%20launch%20an%20attack%20on%20NATO%20within%20the%20next%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETroels%20Lund%20Poulsen%2C%20the%20Danish%20defense%20minister%2C%20told%20the%20Jyllands-Posten%20newspaper%20in%20February%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%20that%20within%20a%20three-%20to%20five-year%20period%2C%20Russia%20will%20test%20Article%205%20and%20NATO's%20solidarity.%20That%20was%20not%20NATO's%20assessment%20in%202023.%20This%20is%20new%20knowledge%20that%20is%20coming%20to%20the%20fore%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-military-almost-complet