n's%20vast%20communications%20network%2C%20and%20after%20its%20dissolution%20in%201991%2C%20the%20transmission%20continued%20to%20operate%20from%20Russian%20territory.%20The%20feed%20has%20gained%20numerous%20followers%20online%2C%20where%20users%20affectionately%20call%20it%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Buzzer%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20numerous%20theories%20around%20the%20radio%20transmission.%20The%20frequency%20is%20thought%20to%20belong%20to%20the%20Russian%20military%2C%20though%20they've%20never%20actually%20admitted%20this%2C%20said%20the%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20believe%20UVB-76%20is%20a%20number%20station%20used%20for%20sending%20coded%20messages%20to%20spies%20and%20operatives.%20The%20cryptic%20voice%20messages%20fit%20the%20pattern%20of%20traditional%20number%20stations%2C%20which%20have%20been%20used%20for%20decades%20by%20various%20countries%20for%20espionage%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20theory%20suggests%20that%20UVB-76%20might%20be%20related%20to%20ionospheric%20research%2C%20helping%20to%20study%20radio%20wave%20propagation%20through%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%20This%20would%20explain%20the%20consistent%20signal%20and%20occasional%20variations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Buzzer%20operates%20at%20a%20relatively%20low%20frequency%20known%20as%20short%20wave%2C%20which%20allows%20it%20to%20travel%20great%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20UVB-76%20has%20undergone%20several%20changes%20that%20have%20reignited%20interest%20and%20speculation.%20In%202010%2C%20a%20significant%20spike%20in%20activity%20included%20more%20frequent%20voice%20messages%2C%20leading%20to%20renewed%20interest%20from%20amateur%20radio%20enthusiasts%20and%20conspiracy%20theorists%20alike%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popularmechanics.com%2Fmilitary%2Fa60857781%2Frussia-radio-signal-the-buzzer-uvb-76%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPopular%20Mechanics%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%2