22%3EJuly%204%20parliamentary%20elections%20in%20the%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20war%20has%20sparked%20large%20protest%20marches%2C%20university%20lecture%20walkouts%20and%20heated%20debates%2C%20profoundly%20influencing%20voter%20sentiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-hamas-gaza-palestine-all-you-need-to-know-about-the-humanitarian-crisis-in-gaza-5593929%5C%22%3EThe%20conflict%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20caused%20rifts%20within%20both%20the%20ruling%20Conservative%20Party%20and%20the%20opposition%20Labour%20Party.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Suella%20Braverman%2C%20an%20Indian-origin%20leader%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party%2C%20was%20forced%20to%20resign%20from%20her%20position%20as%20Home%20Secretary%20after%20calling%20for%20a%20ban%20on%20pro-Palestinian%20protests%20and%20labelling%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Bhate%20marches%26quot%3B.%20While%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20generally%20supports%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20position%20that%20Israel%20has%20a%20right%20to%20defend%20itself%20and%20backs%20his%20call%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20pause%20rather%20than%20a%20full%20ceasefire%2C%20not%20all%20party%20members%20agree%20with%20this%20stance%2C%20which%20some%20see%20as%20pro-Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStarmer%20Faces%20A%20Storm%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Labour%20Party%20has%20been%20hit%20even%20harder%20by%20the%20conflict.%20Leader%20Keir%20Starmer%2C%20who%20seems%20poised%20for%20a%20comfortable%20victory%2C%20faces%20significant%20internal%20opposition.%20Last%20November%2C%20as%20many%20as%2056%20Labour%20MPs%2C%20including%2010%20from%20his%20top%20team%2C%20defied%20his%20order%20to%20abstain%20from%20voting%20on%20a%20parliamentary%20motion%20calling%20for%20a%20ceasefire.%20This%20rebellion%20was%20a%20significant%20blow%20to%20Starmer's%20authority%20as%20he%20tried%20to%20rally%20his%20party%20behind%20his%20stance%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fveteran-uk-minister-latest-to-quit-after-rishi-sunaks-poll-announcement-5740629%5C%22%3EOpinion%20%7C%20Veteran%20UK%20Minister%20Latest%20To%20Quit%20After%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20Poll%20Announcement%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20further%20escalated%20when%20George%20Galloway%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20Workers%20Party%20of%20Britain%2C%20won%20a%20landslide%20victory%20in%20the%20Rochdale%20by-election%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20his%20campaign%20focused%20on%20Israel's%20actions%20in%20Gaza.%20In%20his%20victory%20speech%2C%20Galloway%20declared%2C%20%26quot%3BKeir%20Starmer%2C%20this%20is%20for%20Gaza%26quot%3B%2C%20underscoring%20the%20deep%20divisions%20within%20Labour%20over%20this%20issue.%20He%20polled%20more%20than%20the%20Labour%20and%20Tory%20candidates%20combined.%3Cbr%3E%5CnEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20London%20Mayor%20Sadiq%20Khan%20and%20Manchester%20Mayor%20Andy%20Burnham%20won%20their%20respective%20elections%20while%20breaking%20ranks%20with%20Starmer%20over%20Gaza.%20In%20the%20May%202%20local%20and%20mayoral%20elections%2C%20Labour%20made%20significant%20gains%20but%20underperformed%20in%20areas%20where%20independent%20candidates%20who%20campaigned%20on%20the%20Gaza%20issue%20won%20surprising%20victories.%20George%20Galloway's%20party%20secured%20four%20council%20seats%2C%20defeating%20both%20Labour%20and%20Tory%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%2050%20Labour%20councillors%20have%20resigned%20in%20protest%20against%20Starmer's%20stance%20on%20Gaza%2C%20many%20of%20them%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community%2C%20which%20traditionally%20supports%20Labour.%20Recent%20surveys%20indicate%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20Britons%20favour%20a%20permanent%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%2C%20reflecting%20widespread%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20current%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20Labour%20Return%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccordin